sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1866008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This part has the Super Yellow Fluorescence Protein tagged to the NrfA gene product.
The Promoter+RBS+NrfA construct was obtained from our biobrick BBa_K1866000. The RBS+SYFP construct was procured from the biobrick BBa_K864101.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stefan Oehler

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: P+RBS+NrFA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
The assimilatory Nitrite Reductase gene under the control of a strong Promoter Anderson J23104 with a Ribosome Binding Site was cloned onto the pSB1A3 plasmid backbone. This gene catalyses the conversion of Nitrite (NO2 -) to Ammonium (NH4 +).
The entire cassette can be excised from the backbone and used as per requirement.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stefan Oehler
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
The Promoter+RBS part was obtained from the Biobrick BBa_K880005.
The gene was isolated from Pseudomonas aeruginosa genome. (Refer Biobrick BBa_K1153001)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: None. The sequence is compatible with the 3A assembly recommended by iGEM.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K880005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Strong promoter, strong RBS combination for high expression levels of proteins
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
-J23100+B0034 -Strong promoter, strong RBS combination for high expression levels of proteins
Consensus constitutive promoter and RBS sequence-produces strongest possible expression.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Josh Atkinson, Mike Ferguson, and Ben Parker
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It is a combination of strong promoter (J23100) and RBS (B0034).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K864101
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the <partinfo short>BBa_K864100</partinfo> (<partinfo>BBa_K864100</partinfo>) with the medium strength <partinfo>BBa_B0032</partinfo> RBS. The B0032 RBS is commonly used for promoter testing, giving a wider dynamic range than a stronger RBS.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Arvid Hed??n Gynn??
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Assembly of K864100 and the B0032 from the registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Transcriptional leakage is present in some backbones, giving visibly fluorescent colonies even without promoter.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: SYFP2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for the bright yellow fluorescent protein SYFP2. SYFP2 is a GFP based monomeric protein with a narrow fluorescence emission spectrum with a maximum at 515 nm. Bacteria expressing SYFP2 are reported to be 12 times brighter than those expressing EYFP(Q69K) and almost 2-fold brighter than bacteria expressing Venus (Ref. 10.1021/bi0516273). Codon optimized for expression in E coli by DNA 2.0. Mutations compared to wtGFP amino acid sequence (GenBank Accession number M62653) are F46L F64L S65G S72A M153T V163A S175G T203Y A206K.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erik Gullberg
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Amino acid sequence taken from the article by Kremers et al 2006.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The sequence has been codon optimized for expression in E coli by DNA 2.0.
